  "text": "Thermodynamic stability is an important property that is difficult to investigate in crystallography, but some measure is provided by the nature and the count of hydrogen bonds and the extent of stacking interactions. In this respect, CGG helical structures appear relatively stable compared with CAG and CUG tracts-in agreement with calorimetric studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This could be an important factor in the RNA's ligand binding affinity and specificity.",
